Not fewer than 20 pastors across the dioceses of the Lutheran Church of Christ in Nigeria (LCCN), heralded the end of its national convention in Adamawa state. The Arch Bishop Most Rev.  Musa Panti Filibus  who presided over  the ordination in Demsa charged them to leave an exemplary life for others to emulate. Filibus who is also the President Lutheran World Federation (LWF), noted that, as workers in the vineyard of the Lord , the clergies should be committed to propagating the gospel of Christ through their evangelist activities. He charged the clergies to be cautions of their massages, and should not deviate from the teaching of the lord Almighty rather should teach the truth only that can lead to the kingdom of God. Panti identified purity, humbleness, faithfulness, love, patience and endurance as  significant in the life of believers  while working towards winning the crown of life. The president urged them to stage victorious fight against satan and practice  lifestyle to  influence others around them . He urged the participants to resist the devil and  follow the footsteps of their lord Jesus Christ. He stated that as a living latter in the world, they are responsible for restoration of peace in their various communities and let the light of God shine in them. The man of God,  lamented over the problem of insecurity and the spate of illegal migration saying the church has taken upon itself to embark on enlightenment campaigns against the menace. Highlights of the event was the taking of holy communion by the congregation who attended the convention. 